text: Eva de Goede (born 23 March 1989 in Zeist, Netherlands) is a Dutch field hockey midfielder. She played for the Netherlands women's national field hockey team. With the Netherlands, she won gold medals in the 2008 and 2012 Summer Olympics, as well as in various other tournaments. In 2018 and 2020 she was awarded the FIH Player of the Year.https://www.parool.nl/sport/eva-de- goede-weer-beste-hockeyster-ter-wereld~b73ddaad/ Along with her teammate, Ellen Hoog, de Goede has modeled with Sports Illustrated. == References == Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Olympic gold medalists for the Netherlands Category:Olympic silver medalists for the Netherlands Category:Dutch field hockey players Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Olympics Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics Category:People from Zeist Category:Sportspeople from Utrecht (province)
